DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(5,8,1);
$b1 = random(2,7,1);
$c1 = random(2,5,1);
$x1 = $a1 - $b1*$c1;
$y1 = $a1 + $b1*$c1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
To say that \( \displaystyle \left| \frac {x-$a1 }{$c1} \right| \leq $b1 \) is the same as saying \( x \) is in
the closed interval \( [A,B] \) $BR
where \( A \) is:
\{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $x1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and  where \( B \) is:\{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $y1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

$prod = $b1 * $c1;

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOF'));
$SOL $BR

\( \displaystyle \left| \frac {x-$a1 }{$c1}\right| \leq $b1 \)
$BR
\( \displaystyle \frac{|x-$a1|}{|$c1|} \leq $b1 \)
$BR
\( \displaystyle \frac{|x-$a1|}{$c1} \leq $b1 \)
$BR
\( |x-$a1| \leq $prod \)
$BR
\( - $prod \leq x-$a1 \leq $prod \)
$BR
\( - $prod + $a1 \leq x \leq $prod + $a1 \)
$BR
\( $x1 \leq x \le $y1 \)
$BR
Therefore, \(A= $x1\) and \(B=$y1\).

EOF


ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
